1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:01,870
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,870 --> 00:00:03,610
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,610 --> 00:00:05,180
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:10,450
I found out which school
Baek Jin Ju went to...

5
00:00:10,450 --> 00:00:12,920
and looked through
all their yearbooks.

6
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:14,420
I even found a picture of her.

7
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,520
Nicely done.

8
00:00:17,260 --> 00:00:18,490
Right,

9
00:00:18,590 --> 00:00:20,290
- but something here is weird.
- How so?

10
00:00:20,290 --> 00:00:21,690
Check out her photo.

11
00:00:21,860 --> 00:00:22,860
Her photo?

12
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:26,970
(Personal Profile)

13
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:31,070
(Hanbit High School
62nd Graduation Ceremony)

14
00:00:32,970 --> 00:00:35,040
See? It's weird, right?
It's not just me.

15
00:00:35,610 --> 00:00:38,640
Hey, go on ahead. I've got to run.

16
00:00:45,220 --> 00:00:47,820
Is this what you found
on Dr. Baek's daughter?

17
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:49,390
Yes,

18
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:51,190
but here's the thing.

19
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:54,530
Just brace yourself.

20
00:00:56,530 --> 00:00:59,660
Dr. Baek's daughter and Min Jun
were dating.

21
00:01:00,270 --> 00:01:01,770
What could be more shocking
than that?

22
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:03,900
Tell me about it.

23
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:07,170
But believe me, there's something
even more unbelievable.

24
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:25,020
- An official statement...
- That's absolutely...

25
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:26,120
- will be released shortly.
- not true.

26
00:01:26,190 --> 00:01:27,590
We're still looking into it.

27
00:01:29,660 --> 00:01:31,260
- About the design being stolen?
- What?

28
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:32,600
- Absolutely not.
- The accusation...

29
00:01:32,660 --> 00:01:33,930
is completely false.

30
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,530
At BIT Life,

31
00:01:35,530 --> 00:01:37,640
we prioritize design ethics
above all else.

32
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:41,410
Please avoid
any speculative reporting.

33
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:45,580
This is the new symbol for BIT Life.

34
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:49,810
And this is the design I created.

35
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:52,680
Now, take a look.

36
00:01:55,050 --> 00:01:56,220
This is plagiarism.

37
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:58,490
They stole it from me,
just an unknown designer.

38
00:02:11,140 --> 00:02:12,200
My design book...

39
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,310
is gone.

40
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:20,580
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

41
00:02:28,490 --> 00:02:32,020
The legal team came up with
the quickest way to handle this.

42
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:34,890
Instead of a false accusation,

43
00:02:34,890 --> 00:02:36,960
they're suggesting
we turn it into a real one.

44
00:02:37,660 --> 00:02:38,760
A real one?

45
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:40,930
Chloe stole that design,

46
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:42,970
which made Adele Group
an innocent victim.

47
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:46,170
We pin all the blame...

48
00:02:47,170 --> 00:02:48,210
on Chloe.

49
00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:50,610
Sir, with all due respect...

50
00:02:50,610 --> 00:02:51,610
Besides,

51
00:02:55,510 --> 00:02:57,950
she was disposable from the start.

52
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:00,520
She got cocky and started
ignoring me, the chairman.

53
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:03,420
Such an insolent little thing.

54
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:10,300
This is a chance to show everyone
how ruthless Adele Group can be.

55
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:13,100
We'll make a scapegoat out of Chloe,

56
00:03:14,230 --> 00:03:15,600
and then just start over.

57
00:03:21,010 --> 00:03:22,010
Why the hesitation?

58
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,940
Will you let this project die...

59
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:26,880
and get yourself
kicked out of the company?

60
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,760
Don't overthink it.

61
00:03:38,820 --> 00:03:42,290
Make a decision right now.

62
00:03:48,970 --> 00:03:50,400
Please just give me one day.

63
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,500
If I can't find another solution
within 24 hours,

64
00:03:54,110 --> 00:03:55,610
I'll do as you wish, sir.

65
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:00,510
Why should we waste
even a single day?

66
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:02,710
I'm the one who recruited Chloe.

67
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:05,650
If she's forced out
because of a scandal,

68
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:08,690
I'll be the one held responsible
in the end.

69
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:14,860
Right now, protecting Chloe
is how I protect myself.

70
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:18,900
You have until tomorrow morning.

71
00:04:19,330 --> 00:04:21,300
If you don't have
another solution by then,

72
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:25,200
Chloe's design will be declared
plagiarized. That's that.

73
00:04:47,330 --> 00:04:48,690
Why is there a photo of Chloe?

74
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:57,800
(Personal Profile: Baek Jin Ju)

75
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,270
(Hanbit High School
62nd graduation ceremony)

76
00:04:59,770 --> 00:05:02,510
Why does Dr. Baek's daughter...

77
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:04,580
look like Chloe?

78
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:20,020
(Security Office)

79
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:29,500
Once we prove
your design book was stolen,

80
00:05:30,030 --> 00:05:31,670
you'll be able to clear your name.

81
00:05:38,410 --> 00:05:39,440
But what if...

82
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:42,210
I actually plagiarized it?

83
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:48,850
You never once suspected
I was lying?

84
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:50,390
Never.

85
00:05:54,890 --> 00:05:58,730
From the moment I met you,
I knew you were an honest person.

86
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,930
You're open and direct
in everything you do.

87
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:04,340
That's what makes you so confident.

88
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:09,140
That's who Chloe is, isn't it?

89
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:16,080
You're right.

90
00:06:17,620 --> 00:06:20,080
That's the kind of person Chloe is.

91
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,520
It's ready.

92
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,030
I reviewed the footage...

93
00:06:33,030 --> 00:06:34,670
from when you left
through this morning.

94
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:37,970
Right here.
I noticed something suspicious.

95
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:52,480
No way.

96
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:54,050
Their face is perfectly hidden.

97
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,390
They clearly came in here
planning to steal something.

98
00:06:58,020 --> 00:07:00,220
They knew exactly where
the CCTV cameras were,

99
00:07:00,930 --> 00:07:04,600
and they came in right before
security locked the main entrance.

100
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:08,330
I think it's someone
on the task force.

101
00:07:09,730 --> 00:07:11,100
I was thinking the same thing.

102
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:15,270
Then it could be Manager So,
Assistant Manager Heo,

103
00:07:16,110 --> 00:07:19,910
- or...
- Choi Yu Na.

104
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:30,450
(Head of Division 1, Park Min Jun)

105
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,500
(Personal Profile: Baek Jin Ju)

106
00:07:49,610 --> 00:07:50,940
They don't just look alike.

107
00:07:51,580 --> 00:07:52,980
Their faces are identical.

108
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:02,090
That's why when Chloe first came
to Adele, everyone...

109
00:08:03,490 --> 00:08:04,860
And that's why Min Jun...

110
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:15,630
It's a pleasure to meet you.

111
00:08:19,470 --> 00:08:20,570
I'm Chloe.

112
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:26,510
(Brand Consultant Chloe Lee,
Let Chloe Lee shape Adele's future.)

113
00:08:31,350 --> 00:08:32,420
Just this once,

114
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:35,390
may I hold you?

115
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:46,860
Why is Min Jun...

116
00:08:54,070 --> 00:08:55,110
How...

117
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:58,210
can they look so identical?

118
00:08:59,810 --> 00:09:02,610
I delivered the baby myself,
so I know she doesn't have a twin.

119
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:09,550
You haven't shown your face
this whole time,

120
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:14,530
and I'm sure other companies
have made you better offers.

121
00:09:15,730 --> 00:09:17,830
So why are you
showing yourself now...

122
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:21,070
and partnering with Adele Group?

123
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,270
Because of Temi Bio.

124
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:25,670
No way.

125
00:09:26,940 --> 00:09:27,940
What if...

126
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:30,240
she survived?

127
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:47,460
You called me in
because of that accusation, didn't you?

128
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,730
If by some miracle she survived...

129
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:52,900
and came back for revenge...

130
00:09:54,130 --> 00:09:56,230
If she returned
with a different identity,

131
00:09:57,470 --> 00:09:59,200
just like I did 30 years ago...

132
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,650
Why are you looking at me like that?

133
00:10:16,690 --> 00:10:17,760
Don't tell me...

134
00:10:18,190 --> 00:10:21,390
you actually believe those lies
and suspect me.

135
00:10:25,130 --> 00:10:26,130
Suspect you?

136
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:28,630
Given the circumstances,

137
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:30,170
I have every reason
to be suspicious.

138
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:36,940
Please don't jump to conclusions.

139
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:39,040
We confirmed...

140
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:41,650
that her design book was taken
from the task force office.

141
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:45,180
Once we identify the thief
from the CCTV footage,

142
00:10:45,550 --> 00:10:47,120
the truth will come out.

143
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:51,960
Let's ask the police to investigate
and release the CCTV footage.

144
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:55,660
Whatever it takes,
I want to clear my name.

145
00:11:01,630 --> 00:11:04,440
If it was stolen
from the task force office,

146
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:07,810
it was probably an inside job.

147
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,810
Yes, that's what
the evidence suggests.

148
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:14,950
If an employee is involved,
we have to handle this carefully.

149
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:17,780
If we bring in the police...

150
00:11:17,780 --> 00:11:19,350
without a clear suspect
or any evidence,

151
00:11:19,450 --> 00:11:21,020
it will throw the company
into chaos.

152
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:23,990
I see.

153
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:27,560
So the Adele Group comes before
clearing my name.

154
00:11:28,930 --> 00:11:30,530
I've sent Secretary Jung...

155
00:11:30,530 --> 00:11:32,700
to track down
the person accusing you.

156
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:36,770
Once we find him and get the facts,

157
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:38,800
we'll contact the police
and the press.

158
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:41,910
I just want to be certain
before we act.

159
00:11:42,470 --> 00:11:45,010
If you're innocent,
you can wait one day.

160
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:59,290
You don't seriously suspect Chloe,
do you?

161
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:05,160
Do you trust Chloe completely?

162
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,970
Is it because...

163
00:12:09,970 --> 00:12:11,700
she looks exactly like Baek Jin Ju?

164
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,660
I wonder if we're thinking...

165
00:12:34,260 --> 00:12:35,590
the same thing.

166
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:39,500
What if we're both suspecting
the same person?

167
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,700
Then how about...

168
00:12:42,370 --> 00:12:43,570
we cause a little trouble?

169
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:47,040
I'm more interested in the truth
than playing games.

170
00:12:47,810 --> 00:12:48,810
Will you help me?

171
00:12:56,380 --> 00:12:59,550
That "definitive answer"
you wanted from Chloe...

172
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:04,620
was really about figuring out
if she's Baek Jin Ju, wasn't it?

173
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:07,390
Yes. But...

174
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:12,260
As you might have guessed,

175
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,730
Chloe isn't Jin Ju.

176
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:19,070
Choi Yu Na even had Chloe
and James' DNA tested.

177
00:13:20,340 --> 00:13:22,310
Ms. Choi had their DNA tested?

178
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:25,140
She was probably afraid
I'd think Chloe was Jin Ju,

179
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:28,150
so she made sure I knew for certain.

180
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,880
Are you sure about the test results?

181
00:13:30,980 --> 00:13:32,250
I checked them myself.

182
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:38,960
The whole Jin Ju thing aside,
Chloe would never plagiarize.

183
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:41,060
She really wants
to find the real culprit...

184
00:13:41,060 --> 00:13:43,060
and prove her innocence,

185
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:45,600
so please help her.

186
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:55,270
You've already concluded
that she's just Chloe.

187
00:13:56,010 --> 00:13:58,680
But is she really?

188
00:13:59,540 --> 00:14:01,710
Could she be Baek Jin Ju,
back for revenge...

189
00:14:02,210 --> 00:14:03,910
under a different identity?

190
00:14:15,090 --> 00:14:16,960
(Team Leader, Choi Yu Na)

191
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:21,500
Have you checked the CCTV footage?

192
00:14:21,870 --> 00:14:26,600
Yes. We have footage of someone
stealing the design book.

193
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,770
Does that mean
you identified the thief?

194
00:14:29,570 --> 00:14:32,440
Their face was covered
by a hoodie and a mask,

195
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:34,280
so you can't really make it out.

196
00:14:34,650 --> 00:14:37,510
Does that mean
they'll get away with this?

197
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:41,820
The video won't help much,
but we have another angle.

198
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:46,120
My dad is going to catch the person
who made that broadcast.

199
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:49,430
He said he's already...

200
00:14:50,330 --> 00:14:51,360
identified the man.

201
00:14:51,860 --> 00:14:55,070
Goodness.
Your dad's very resourceful.

202
00:14:55,470 --> 00:14:58,740
We'll catch him and ask
where he got the design book.

203
00:15:00,140 --> 00:15:02,370
Then it's game over.

204
00:15:07,810 --> 00:15:09,210
President Kim also...

205
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:12,750
sent Secretary Jung to track him,

206
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:14,690
so he'll be caught soon.

207
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:31,170
Choi Yu Na. I knew it was you.

208
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:34,840
I thought you'd stand up
to Park Tae Ho...

209
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,340
after your wedding was canceled.

210
00:15:37,810 --> 00:15:39,880
But was petty revenge
really your first move?

211
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:45,920
Or are you just too scared
to stand up to Chairman Park?

212
00:15:52,190 --> 00:15:53,760
Why isn't he answering his phone?

213
00:15:55,430 --> 00:15:56,860
The person you have called...

214
00:16:12,780 --> 00:16:13,880
What do you think you're doing?

215
00:16:14,410 --> 00:16:15,510
Give it back.

216
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:20,650
Your call history
could be useful evidence.

217
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:28,290
You can hide your face,

218
00:16:28,490 --> 00:16:30,260
but you can't hide your guilt.

219
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:35,170
Once they catch your accomplice,

220
00:16:35,530 --> 00:16:39,070
everything you've done
will come to light.

221
00:16:45,210 --> 00:16:46,610
What nonsense is this?

222
00:16:48,010 --> 00:16:50,310
What does this have to do with me?

223
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,250
Where's your proof?

224
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:58,120
Fine. Go ahead and try to hide
your guilt and the evidence.

225
00:16:59,020 --> 00:17:02,030
If the chairman finds out
you've damaged Adele's reputation,

226
00:17:02,260 --> 00:17:04,090
he might just kick you out.

227
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:11,870
If you don't have the guts
to stand up to Chairman Park,

228
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:15,510
I'll force you into a corner
where you have no other choice.

229
00:17:16,510 --> 00:17:18,540
If you don't want to be thrown away
by Park Tae Ho,

230
00:17:20,380 --> 00:17:22,110
you'd better fight back
with everything you've got.

231
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,600
Hey!

232
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:43,970
Hey, get back here!

233
00:17:43,970 --> 00:17:45,200
You punk!

234
00:17:45,940 --> 00:17:47,570
- Hey!
- Stop right there!

235
00:17:48,270 --> 00:17:50,310
Get back here. Hey, you punk!

236
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:52,510
Hey!

237
00:17:52,610 --> 00:17:54,240
You're dead if I catch you.

238
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:59,080
I'm going to tear you
limb from limb, you punk!

239
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:01,550
I told you to stop!

240
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:09,860
What...

241
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:12,960
Darn it.

242
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,130
Gosh, that hurts.

243
00:18:19,940 --> 00:18:21,610
My gosh.

244
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:24,880
What were you thinking,
falling over like that?

245
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:27,640
I'm sorry about that.

246
00:18:31,050 --> 00:18:32,550
That little punk.

247
00:18:34,890 --> 00:18:37,320
We almost had him.

248
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:40,160
I'm sorry.

249
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:43,760
Did you hurt yourself when you fell?

250
00:18:44,060 --> 00:18:45,800
I'm fine.

251
00:18:49,730 --> 00:18:52,470
Your arm seems okay.
Let me check your leg.

252
00:18:54,340 --> 00:18:56,010
Stop it.

253
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:58,280
Seriously.

254
00:18:58,440 --> 00:19:00,640
Stop groping him.

255
00:19:00,710 --> 00:19:03,680
I was just checking to see
if he hurt his leg.

256
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:06,480
That doesn't mean
you can just feel up a guy's leg.

257
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:08,520
Hold on a second.

258
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:11,660
Are you two close enough
to be this touchy-feely?

259
00:19:13,620 --> 00:19:15,260
Of course we are.

260
00:19:16,330 --> 00:19:17,330
What?

261
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,730
We're comrades
who just fought side by side.

262
00:19:20,730 --> 00:19:22,170
He's hurt,

263
00:19:22,170 --> 00:19:24,570
so it's my duty to look after him.

264
00:19:26,170 --> 00:19:27,370
Right, sure.

265
00:19:27,740 --> 00:19:29,670
Your duty.

266
00:19:29,670 --> 00:19:34,310
I'm against all of it.
This duty, the touching, and him.

267
00:19:34,510 --> 00:19:35,510
Get up already.

268
00:19:35,510 --> 00:19:37,250
- What?
- I said get up.

269
00:19:37,250 --> 00:19:38,520
- Come on.
- But...

270
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:40,850
- Not with my sister.
- It's not like that.

271
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,920
- Get going.
- But....

272
00:19:42,690 --> 00:19:44,120
You're here.

273
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:00,800
I heard you got hurt,
so I stopped by.

274
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,210
Are you okay?

275
00:20:04,270 --> 00:20:05,640
I'm fine.

276
00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:09,510
But I'm the reason he got away.

277
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:11,780
I feel terrible for Chloe,

278
00:20:12,350 --> 00:20:14,250
and I sincerely apologize, ma'am.

279
00:20:14,890 --> 00:20:15,890
Not at all.

280
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:18,190
I'm just glad
you weren't seriously hurt.

281
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:21,730
Your daughter and your family
would've been worried sick.

282
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:24,530
Wait a second.

283
00:20:25,860 --> 00:20:28,770
A daughter? So you're married?

284
00:20:29,670 --> 00:20:33,140
Seriously? You were feeling up
a married man's leg?

285
00:20:33,270 --> 00:20:34,940
No. Gosh, no.

286
00:20:35,310 --> 00:20:38,110
I'm not. I'm as single as it gets.

287
00:20:38,940 --> 00:20:40,540
Chloe's mother and I...

288
00:20:41,180 --> 00:20:42,180
split up...

289
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:44,980
a very long time ago,

290
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:47,750
and I've been raising Chloe
all on my own...

291
00:20:48,050 --> 00:20:49,920
ever since.

292
00:20:50,620 --> 00:20:52,160
I see.

293
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:53,920
It must've been tough.

294
00:20:54,220 --> 00:20:55,330
You have no idea.

295
00:20:56,390 --> 00:20:58,660
Running a business in the US
and raising a kid.

296
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:01,470
Just thinking back on it...

297
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:05,240
I'm laughing,
but I feel like I'm crying.

298
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,410
Thinking back...

299
00:21:08,610 --> 00:21:09,710
Unbelievable.

300
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:14,810
To learn more about Chloe,

301
00:21:14,810 --> 00:21:17,750
I'll need information
about her life in the US.

302
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:30,290
Looks like our dear chairman
has lost his appetite.

303
00:21:30,930 --> 00:21:31,930
I'm not surprised.

304
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:35,530
That witch Kim Myung Hui
brought in some delinquent...

305
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:38,140
and dragged the Adele Group's reputation
through the mud.

306
00:21:40,370 --> 00:21:43,440
What? Did all that talk
make you lose your appetite?

307
00:21:44,510 --> 00:21:46,040
That's disgusting.

308
00:21:46,980 --> 00:21:51,480
How can I eat when you're talking
nonsense at the dinner table?

309
00:21:51,850 --> 00:21:54,480
- Darn it.
- My, was I doing that?

310
00:21:54,950 --> 00:21:57,750
I was just trying
to lighten your mood.

311
00:21:57,850 --> 00:22:00,190
If you're going to lie,
at least make it believable.

312
00:22:00,190 --> 00:22:02,730
You don't know your head
from your feet.

313
00:22:03,090 --> 00:22:06,900
All you care about is the thrill
of talking trash about others.

314
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:11,370
It was just a joke.
Nothing to bite my head off over.

315
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:15,170
Besides, you let that Kim Myung Hui
get away with causing a huge mess.

316
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:25,280
See?

317
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:27,250
Because you just let her do
whatever she wants,

318
00:22:27,350 --> 00:22:29,890
she's practically beaming
despite all the trouble she's caused.

319
00:22:30,420 --> 00:22:31,520
It's so irritating.

320
00:22:31,790 --> 00:22:35,730
If you're that jealous,
then go live in the annex.

321
00:22:36,030 --> 00:22:38,830
I'll be sure to leave you alone
for the rest of your life.

322
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:42,670
Hold on a second.
You think I'm jealous?

323
00:22:43,270 --> 00:22:44,940
I've never been jealous of her.

324
00:22:45,340 --> 00:22:47,870
I'm not bad-looking myself.
Unbelievable.

325
00:22:47,940 --> 00:22:50,170
Darn it.

326
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:51,840
There's something...

327
00:22:53,540 --> 00:22:55,110
I'd like to say.

328
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:13,900
Let me get this straight.

329
00:23:15,470 --> 00:23:17,700
You haven't caught the thief
who stole the design book...

330
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:21,040
or the person
who's falsely accusing Chloe,

331
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:23,970
but I'm supposed to let her be?

332
00:23:24,170 --> 00:23:27,980
Chloe saw the CCTV footage herself,
and she has a copy.

333
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:31,280
If she's treated unfairly,
she'll release the footage...

334
00:23:31,380 --> 00:23:32,980
and even go after Adele.

335
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,890
So what's your solution?

336
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:44,460
We'll request a police investigation
and disclose the facts to the media.

337
00:23:45,430 --> 00:23:49,270
So you're going to advertise
that there's a thief inside Adele?

338
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:52,370
This will show that Adele
handles wrongdoing decisively,

339
00:23:52,370 --> 00:23:53,670
even when it's an insider,

340
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:58,210
and that we're a fair
and honest company.

341
00:24:00,210 --> 00:24:02,980
It'll also help restore our image,

342
00:24:02,980 --> 00:24:04,480
which was damaged
by the false accusation.

343
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:17,460
Manager Kang.

344
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:20,430
Use our police contacts
to request an investigation.

345
00:24:22,130 --> 00:24:24,730
The thief inside Adele...

346
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:27,240
and the scumbag
who made false accusations.

347
00:24:28,510 --> 00:24:29,870
Round them all up.

348
00:24:42,420 --> 00:24:43,420
My gosh!

349
00:24:44,190 --> 00:24:45,590
Keep it down.

350
00:24:45,660 --> 00:24:46,920
Seriously.

351
00:24:47,420 --> 00:24:50,760
Ms. Oh, why are you
always up to no good?

352
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:54,130
Does everything your mother does
look bad to you?

353
00:24:54,730 --> 00:24:56,570
I was keeping an eye on things,

354
00:24:56,570 --> 00:24:59,000
worried that the witch
would win his favor...

355
00:24:59,070 --> 00:25:00,270
and get off scotch-free.

356
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:03,240
It's "scot-free," not "scotch-free."

357
00:25:03,740 --> 00:25:06,640
Scot, scotch, whatever.
I don't see the difference.

358
00:25:07,010 --> 00:25:08,250
Ms. Oh, wait.

359
00:25:08,750 --> 00:25:10,910
Come on, you need to learn
to read the room.

360
00:25:11,450 --> 00:25:13,920
Right. Read the room.

361
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:16,250
Know when to get involved
and when not to.

362
00:25:16,350 --> 00:25:17,820
Now is the time to get involved.

363
00:25:17,950 --> 00:25:19,790
Absolutely not.

364
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:21,020
You should stay out of it.

365
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:22,990
It's not your fight,

366
00:25:22,990 --> 00:25:25,200
even if President Kim
is getting her way.

367
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:27,460
Because this wasn't...

368
00:25:27,460 --> 00:25:29,400
President Kim's fault
in the first place.

369
00:25:30,270 --> 00:25:31,370
What do you mean by that?

370
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,210
The person
who stole the design book...

371
00:25:35,210 --> 00:25:36,770
and orchestrated
the false accusation?

372
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:39,010
It was Choi Yu Na.

373
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:40,580
I'm absolutely certain.

374
00:25:40,940 --> 00:25:41,950
Ms. Choi?

375
00:25:43,050 --> 00:25:44,780
What does she have to do with this?

376
00:25:44,950 --> 00:25:46,750
It seems
her engagement's been called off,

377
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:48,220
so she's lashing out.

378
00:25:49,850 --> 00:25:51,250
Once
the police investigation begins,

379
00:25:51,250 --> 00:25:53,520
she'll totally lose it out of fear.

380
00:25:54,490 --> 00:25:57,790
So, Ms. Oh,
how about you sit this one out?

381
00:25:57,960 --> 00:26:01,670
Don't jump in
and cause trouble again. Got it?

382
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:12,080
So, this is all Ms. Choi's doing?

383
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:15,250
Then this is a game
I can't possibly sit out.

384
00:26:16,350 --> 00:26:18,320
Hey, bring the car around.

385
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:20,080
What?

386
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:24,290
Where could we be going
at this hour?

387
00:26:41,910 --> 00:26:43,840
I've reported it to the chairman.

388
00:26:44,310 --> 00:26:46,040
The police are going
to start an investigation.

389
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:49,780
Okay. I'll pass that along to Chloe.

390
00:26:57,950 --> 00:26:59,090
Thank you...

391
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:00,760
for your help.

392
00:27:03,490 --> 00:27:04,590
I was wondering...

393
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,500
about Baek Jin Ju.

394
00:27:09,370 --> 00:27:10,770
Is there anything
unique about her...

395
00:27:11,330 --> 00:27:14,070
that sets her apart from Chloe?

396
00:27:17,370 --> 00:27:20,080
I've already given up on the idea...

397
00:27:20,710 --> 00:27:21,880
that Chloe could be Jin Ju.

398
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:24,980
There's no need
to concern yourself with it.

399
00:27:42,930 --> 00:27:46,040
(Personal Profile: Baek Jin Ju)

400
00:28:00,180 --> 00:28:01,650
Hello, ma'am.

401
00:28:02,250 --> 00:28:03,620
I know it's been a while.

402
00:28:04,650 --> 00:28:06,520
I was hoping
to meet briefly tomorrow.

403
00:28:06,820 --> 00:28:07,820
Would that be possible?

404
00:28:23,010 --> 00:28:24,040
Secretary Jung, wait.

405
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:28,010
What happened to the person
who made the false accusation?

406
00:28:28,750 --> 00:28:30,450
Well, the thing is,

407
00:28:31,310 --> 00:28:33,120
we almost had him, but he got away.

408
00:28:33,980 --> 00:28:36,720
If James hadn't fallen over,
we would've caught him for sure.

409
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:40,320
So you went with Chloe's father?

410
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:43,360
We just happened to meet
in front of the suspect's house.

411
00:28:44,130 --> 00:28:45,900
I'm impressed with his intel.

412
00:28:46,460 --> 00:28:48,200
I wish I could say the same
about his stamina.

413
00:28:50,530 --> 00:28:53,570
Could you give me
the suspect's address?

414
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:09,790
Hey. What are you doing here?

415
00:29:10,120 --> 00:29:13,460
I heard the false accuser got away,
so I stopped by.

416
00:29:14,660 --> 00:29:16,060
Looks like you beat me to it.

417
00:29:17,830 --> 00:29:19,500
Aren't you scared
being here all by yourself?

418
00:29:20,100 --> 00:29:21,100
No.

419
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:24,900
I'm not the least bit scared
of some liar.

420
00:29:54,230 --> 00:29:55,870
If I really get caught...

421
00:30:07,140 --> 00:30:09,250
You can't just show up like this!

422
00:30:09,250 --> 00:30:10,350
You!

423
00:30:12,550 --> 00:30:13,920
This is all your fault.

424
00:30:14,780 --> 00:30:16,120
You said no one would find out.

425
00:30:16,120 --> 00:30:17,450
You said everything would be fine.

426
00:30:17,550 --> 00:30:19,590
I got doxxed, and now people
are showing up at my house.

427
00:30:20,590 --> 00:30:22,290
How are you going to fix this?

428
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:24,530
Fix what?

429
00:30:29,970 --> 00:30:31,830
Why should I fix anything?

430
00:30:32,470 --> 00:30:36,010
You were more than happy
to do it for money.

431
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:39,140
So you're just going to bail on me?

432
00:30:40,780 --> 00:30:42,680
If I get caught
by the police or Adele,

433
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,580
do you think
you'll get away scot-free?

434
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:46,620
So just...

435
00:30:48,620 --> 00:30:50,150
lay low.

436
00:30:53,460 --> 00:30:54,490
Then pay up.

437
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:57,890
Everything costs money
when you're in hiding.

438
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:00,000
A hundred grand should do it.

439
00:31:00,700 --> 00:31:02,830
What, 100,000 dollars?

440
00:31:02,830 --> 00:31:05,130
Move fast,
or become a jobless criminal.

441
00:31:05,900 --> 00:31:08,000
You don't want me
to say "screw this," get caught,

442
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:11,440
and spill everything.

443
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:36,170
Well, now.

444
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:41,970
Looks like I stumbled upon
something interesting.

445
00:32:16,840 --> 00:32:19,910
(Pearl in Red)

446
00:32:20,210 --> 00:32:23,380
I'm hoping to get information
about these two people.

447
00:32:23,450 --> 00:32:26,020
If Baek Jin Ju has returned
as Chloe,

448
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:27,650
- is that something to celebrate...
- Dad!

449
00:32:27,650 --> 00:32:28,990
or fear?

450
00:32:29,090 --> 00:32:32,990
You shouldn't be so cocky
when I'm the one holding your leash.

451
00:32:33,060 --> 00:32:34,220
Are you threatening me?

452
00:32:34,220 --> 00:32:35,760
Do you still not get it?

453
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:38,360
You have to pay
for stepping so far out of line.

454
00:32:39,700 --> 00:32:41,700
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
